					<ul class="style__ul_cont">
						<li>
							<div class="title_ul_g">I am returning to Ukraine from abroad, what do I need?</div>
							<div class="subtitle_ul_g">Regardless of the country of arrival, all Ukrainians must either have a negative PCR test done a maximum of 48 hours before entry, or install the application Vdoma for two-week self-isolation. It is possible to stop self-isolation early if you do a PCR test and get a negative result.</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<div class="title_ul_g">Does my child need a test?</div>
							<div class="subtitle_ul_g">Children under 12 do not need a test or self-isolation.</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<div class="title_ul_g">What are the regulations of entry to Ukraine for citizens of Ukraine for the purpose of transit?</div>
							<div class="subtitle_ul_g">To cross the border of Ukraine in transit, a Ukrainian must have a negative PCR test done no more than 48 hours before entry.</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<div class="title_ul_g">I’m traveling without a test, when do I install the application Vdoma?</div>
							<div class="subtitle_ul_g">You can install the application Vdoma on your phone whenever it is convenient for you. And you need to log in directly at the border control when you have already crossed the border of Ukraine.</div>
						</li>
						<li>
							<div class="title_ul_g">How much time do I have to get to the place of self-isolation?</div>
							<div class="subtitle_ul_g">From the moment you cross the border, you have 24 hours to get to the indicated place of self-isolation.</div>
						</li>
					</ul>
